  "stories": [
    {
      "ticker": "BA",
      "score": 95,
      "action": "BUY",
      "entity": "THE BOEING COMPANY",
      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: Boeing / NASA Contract Awards\n\n**The Boeing Company (BA) received two NASA contracts totaling approximately $32.9 billion** — individually valued at $22.4 billion and $10.5 billion — representing among the largest NASA procurement awards in recent agency history, awarded to a contractor with an established record of federal oversight scrutiny.\n\n**Boeing has maintained continuous lobbying expenditures exceeding $15 million annually** and has contributed to members of the Senate Commerce Committee and House Science, Space, and Technology Committee, the bodies with direct appropriations and oversight authority over NASA's budget and contract authorizations.\n\n**The Space Launch System (SLS) program, Boeing's primary NASA vehicle contract, has been subject to multiple Government Accountability Office findings** citing cost overruns exceeding $6 billion beyond original projections and schedule delays spanning years, yet contract modifications continued to expand the program's total obligated value without competitive rebidding.\n\n**Boeing's federal contracting history reflects a documented pattern**: the company paid $2.5 billion to resolve a DOJ criminal conspiracy charge in 2021 related to the 737 MAX, faced repeated FAA safety findings in 2023-2024, and remains under active Senate investigation — while continuing to receive sole-source and non-competitive NASA contract awards, consistent with a pattern identified by federal watchdogs of contractors retaining major government business despite unresolved compliance and safety violations.\n\n*Sources: NASA procurement records, GAO reports, DOJ settlement records, Senate Commerce Committee filings, OpenSecrets lobbying data.*"
    }
  ],
